The '''L-hand 980''' was a [[Cybernetics/Legends|prosthetic]] [[Limb/Legends|hand]] model produced by [[Antilles BioGen]] (ABG). The model was used by [[Medical droid/Legends|medical droid]] [[2-1B/Legends|2-1B]] to replace [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] hand after it was [[Duel on Cloud City/Legends|lost]] on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] when fighting against his father, [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]].

ABG later discontinued the arm that went with the hand, but 2-1B suggested the [[J2J model prosthetic arm]] from [[Organa Organics]].

==Behind the scenes==
The L-hand 980, Antilles BioGen, the J2J, and Organa Organics were all first mentioned by a bitter 2-1B in [[Star Wars Insider 51|''Star Wars Insider'' 51]] in the [[Dear 2-1B]] column.

